<HEAD>Two Hospitalized After Corned Beef And Cabbage Dinner</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WORCESTER, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   City health officials say 25 people
became ill and two had to be hospitalized following a corned beef
and cabbage dinner sponsored by the Ancient Order of Hibernians.
   Richard Wilberg, chief inspector for the city Department of
Public Health, said Tuesday that the meat served at the Saturday
