<2ND_LINE>PM-Children Killed,0192</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three Children Die In Submerged Van</HEAD>
<DATELINE>POINT CLEAR, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three children died today when a van
ran off a coastal road and plunged into the chilly waters of Weeks
Bay, where it remained submerged for three hours, state troopers
said.
   A woman driving the van escaped and was taken by helicopter to
the University of South Alabama Medical Center, where she was being
questioned byb authorities.
   The driver was identified as 29-year-old Aimee Dees of Chatom.
The children were not immediately identified.
   State troopers said the van apparently ran off a county road
between 1 a.m. and 1:30 a.m.The road dead-ends into the secluded
bay, about seven miles south of Point Clear.
   A group of people on the beach near the county road were huddled
around a campfire when they saw the van run into the water. They
pulled Mrs. Dees out, but didn't know the children were still in
the vehicle.
   Mrs. Dees was dazed and in shock and unable to immediately
describe what happened, authorities said.
   Rescue workers searched in 30-degree weather for three hours
before locating the vehicle.
