<HEAD>Auditor Plans Hunt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LITTLE ROCK, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   When Sidney Moncrief graduated from the
University of Arkansas, he left behind a sterling record as a
basketball player and $8.31.
   The Milwaukee Bucks' star is one of the 2,494 Arkansans who have
money in accounts that have been inactive for seven years. State
Auditor Julia Jones is trying to track them down through a
publicity campaign beginning this month.
   The booty is more than $750,000 in wages, bank accounts,
insurance payments, utility deposits and other monies.
   Nancy L. Thornton, who heads the auditor's Unclaimed Property
Division, said that in some instances, the owners simply had not
touched their accounts for seven years and the money is not
actually unclaimed.
   Moncrief's $8.31? Seems he forgot about a electric utility
deposit from his school days.
