<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--MultipleBirths     03-16 0109</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Multiple Births,0110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Multiple Births Increase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Multiple births increased slightly in the United
States from 1984 to 1985, according to insurance company figures
issued Wednesday.
   Multiple births were up 6 percent during the period _ although
they still accounted for only 2.1 percent of the 3.7 million
recorded live births, according to the Statistical Bulletin, a
quarterly publication produced by the Metropolitan Life Insurance
Co.
   Most of the multiple births were twins. However, fertility drugs
have slightly increased the odds for triplets, the report said. In
1985, 2.5 percent of multiple births involved three or more babies
_ up from 2.1 percent in 1983.
</TEXT>
