to be the Republican nominee.''
   Indiana will have 51 delegates at the GOP convention, with 30 of
them at stake in the primary.
   Among those joining Orr in expressing support for Bush were
state Republican Chairman Gordon K. Durnil and Marion County
Prosecutor Stephen Goldsmith. Durnil previously had been neutral in
the presidential race.
