<HEAD>Korean Investment Overseas Top $1 Billion Since 1962</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Aggregate overseas equity investment
by South Korean companies since 1962 totaled $1 billion as of the
end of February, the Finance Ministry reported Wednesday.
   Ministry officials said it was the first time the cumulative
tally topped the $1 billion mark since 1962 Korean companies began
investing abroad in 1962.
   They said about one-third of the total went to the United States
for manufacturing and other projects.
   Officials also said Korean investment abroad had shown marked
rises in the past two years, reflecting the country's growing
current account surplus, with $157 million invested in 1986 and
$397 million in 1987.
   Ministry statistics indicated foreign equity investment in South
Korea since 1962 was a cumulative $3.92 billion as of the end of
January, after deducting withdrawals over the period.
