<HEAD>London Stocks Down 9 Points</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices fell Wednesday amid concerns about
British monetary policy following Tuesday's fiscal 1989 budget
announcement.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange index of 100 stocks was down
9 points, or 0.5 percent, at 1,830.9 at midday.
   Volume was a moderate 314.1 million shares, compared with 241.3
million shares the same time Tuesday.
   Concerns focused on the strength of the pound and perceptions
that the next move in British interest rates likely would be higher.
