corporate profitability. The budget announcement did little to
dispel these fears, dealers said.
   Also hitting share prices was profit-taking following strong
gains posted in the run-up to the budget announcement, dealers said.
   They added that prices were being marked down amid light volume
as the market awaits Thursday's release of U.S. trade figures for
January.
   ``With U.S. trade figures tomorrow, I don't think I'd be an
aggressive buyer either,'' said Nicholas Knight, an equities
strategist at James Capel and Co.
