<HEAD>Sony Introduces CD Player Just For Small Disks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sony Corp. on Wednesday introduced the first
compact disk player designed specifically for the new 3-inch
compact disks.
   The new D-88 Pocket Discman is smaller than a person's hand and
can also play standard 5-inch CDs, although the larger disks stick
out one side like a slice of salami in a sandwich.
   The D-88 will be available in June at a suggested retail price
of $359.95, Sony said.
   The 3-inch CDs can hold up to 20 minutes of music. They have
been available since late last year and can be played on most
standard-sized players.
   Separately, Sony said its Digital Audio Disc Corp. of Terre
Haute, Ind., expects to deliver 1.5 million of the 3-inch disks per
month by later this year.
</TEXT>
