<2ND_LINE>BC-Board of Trade, Close,0180</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Most grain and soybean futures prices turned
weaker today on the Chicago Board of Trade.
   Hedge selling from South America put pressure on the soybean
market from the start, said Jerry Gidel, an analyst with G.H.
Miller & Co.
   This was compounded by industry data putting the soybean crush
figure for February at 3.7 million tons, substantially lower than a
