markets, said Gidel.
   On the close, wheat was 3 cents lower to { cent higher with the
contract for delivery in March at $2.92{ a bushel; corn was \ cent
to 1\ cents lower with March at $1.97{ a bushel; oats were } cent
lower to 1 cent higher with March at $1.89{ a bushel; and soybeans
were 2\ cents to 4{ cents lower with March at $6.11{ a bushel.
